va linux systems inc will exit the hardware business by the end of july to focus on application software and consulting services the company said yesterday va linux based in freemont calif sells servers and workstations designed for use with the linux operating system it also announced plans to lay off 35 percent of its 436 employees va linux which posted a third quarter loss of 110 million on revenue of 203 million said that it planned to focus on technology that helps software developers collaborate on large projects its shares closed at 326 down 3 cents after trading was halted for the news susan stellin nyt

